  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Citizens&apos; Engagement on Issues of Public Interest</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A pilot project over a 9-month implementation of the British Council with its partner Trag Foundation, aimed at supporting civil society organisations and grass-root initiatives in local communities Serbia in order to improve their capabilities to engage citizens more actively in holding authorities to account.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Civil society organisations, grass-root organisations, local communities and citizens themselves.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project outcomes: CSOs have knowledge and skills to actively engage with citizens and articulate their interests; and CSOs are perceived by citizens as more transparent and legitimate.</narrative>
  </description>
